label: TYPE
description: This field stores a code that determines how the system uses the IRS Distribution record for dividends, maturity, or teller transactions.

label: EFFECTIVEDATE
description: This field stores the date on which the IRS Distribution record should take effect.

label: EXPIRATIONDATE
description: This field stores the date to expire this IRS Distribution record.

label: RECORDCHANGEDATE
description: The system stores the system date in this field when you create, change, or save the IRS Distribution record. Sometimes the system updates this field because the record was saved, even though there may not be any actual changes in the record.

label: AMOUNT
description: This field stores the required distribution amount based on the IRA Required Minimum Distribution (RMD) edit run calculation.

label: DISTRIBUTIONCODE
description: This field stores a code that identifies the distribution code to use for the withdrawal.

label: FEDWHOLDCODE
description: This field stores a code that determines how the system handles federal withholding for this distribution.

label: FEDWHOLDPERCENT
description: This field stores the percentage the system should withhold for federal withholding.

label: FEDWHOLDAMOUNT
description: This field stores a dollar amount for how much the system should withhold federal withholding.

label: STATEWHOLDCODE
description: This field stores a code that determines how the system handles state withholding for this distribution.

label: STATEWHOLDPERCENT
description: This field stores the percentage the system should withhold for state withholding.

label: STATEWHOLDAMOUNT
description: This field stores a dollar amount for how much the system should withhold state withholding.

label: DISTRIBUTIONMETHOD
description: This field is used only for IRS Distribution records with a value in the IRS Distribution Type field of (0) Auto Distribution. This field stores a code that indicates how the distribution should be handled.

label: DESTINATIONACCOUNT
description: This field is used only for IRS Distribution records with a value in the IRS Distribution Type field of (0) Auto Distribution and a value in the Distribution Method field of (1) Transfer. This field stores the account number associated with the share to which you are transferring funds.

label: DESTINATIONID
description: This field is used only for IRS Distribution records with a value in the IRS Distribution Type field of (0) Auto Distribution and a value in the Distribution Method field of (1) Transfer. This field stores the share ID to which you are transferring funds.

label: DISTRIBUTIONFREQ
description: This field is used only for IRS Distribution records with a value in the IRS Distribution Type field of (0) Auto Distribution. This field stores a code that defines how often the distribution should occur.

label: DISTRIBUTIONDAY1
description: This field is used only for IRS Distribution records with a value in the IRS Distribution Type field of (0) Auto Distribution. This field stores the day of the month on which you want the automatic distribution to take place for annual, semiannual, quarterly, monthly, or semimonthly transfers.

label: DISTRIBUTIONDAY2
description: This field is used only for IRS Distribution records with a value in the IRS Distribution Type field of (0) Auto Distribution. This field stores the day of the month on which you want a second distribution day within a month for semimonthly transfers.

label: REGE
description: This field is used only for IRS Distribution records with a value in the IRS Distribution Type field of (0) Auto Distribution and a value in the Distribution Method field of (1) Transfer. This field stores a code that indicates if the transfer be flagged as Reg E or not.

label: NEXTDISTRIBUTNDATE
description: This field is used only for IRS Distribution records with a value in the IRS Distribution Type field of (0) Auto Distribution. This field stores the date of the next automatic share distribution.

label: LASTDISTRIBUTNAMT
description: This field stores the total amount of the distribution whenever the system performs certain distributions.

label: LASTDISTRIBUTNDATE
description: This field stores the transaction posting date of the distribution whenever the system performs certain distributions.

label: SOURCEID:1
description: These fields are used only for IRS Distribution records with a value in the IRS Distribution Type field of (0) Auto Distribution. These fields store share IDs in the same account that you can use as source shares for IRS distributions.
